http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Man-hacked-to-death-in-Kalaburagi/article14013277.ece

A 29-year-old man was hacked to death by two persons who came by a motorcycle here on Thursday.The police gave the name of the victim as Kirtikumar. He was proceeding towards the government general hospital in his motorcycle when two unidentified assailants attacked him from the behind with swords and other weapons and hacked him to death. Kirtikumar received multiple injuries on his face, neck and lower abdomen, and died on the spot after profusely bleeding. Even as the onlookers could fathom the brutal murder, the assailants escaped in their motorcycle. Kirtikumar was a close relative of Bombay Sanjay, a gangster who has been lodged in the high security Hindalga Jail in Belagavi. Senior police officers, including Superintendent of Police Amit Singh, and Additional Superintendent of Police Jayaprakash, inspected the spot. The body was shifted to the government hospital for post-mortem.